Arrays

Memory Address

the type of the array determines amount of memory allocation

# of consecutive bytes depends on the variable type

Can have primitive types and reference types

Arrays are considered to be objects -> reference types

Class Arrays
    - Provides static methods for common array operations
    - Array.sort() sorts an array in decreasing order
    - .binarySearch of a sorted array
    - .equals compares two arrays
    - .fill fills an array with values

<code>
    double[] array = new double[24];
    Color[] array = new Color[24];
    methodName(array, otherArguments); // The called method receives a copy of hte reference ot the array
    methodName(array[5], otherArguments); // The called method receives a copy of the array indexes value